getBreadCrumbTitle().Description: Return the full bread crumb title for the entry, or null if it does not have one.

getBreadCrumbShortTitle().Description: Return the short bread crumb title for the entry, or null if it does not have one.

getId().Description: Return the unique identifier for the entry. This is the only representation of the entry that will persist across activity instances.

getBreadCrumbShortTitleRes().Description: Return the short bread crumb title resource identifier for the entry, or 0 if it does not have one.

getName().Description: Get the name that was supplied to @B_android#support#v4#app#FragmentTransaction#addToBackStack_E@ when creating this entry.

getBreadCrumbTitleRes().Description: Return the full bread crumb title resource identifier for the entry, or 0 if it does not have one.

ClassDesc: Representation of an entry on the fragment back stack, as created with @B_android#support#v4#app#FragmentTransaction#addToBackStack_E@. Entries can later be retrieved with @B_android#support#v4#app#FragmentManager#getBackStackEntryAt_E@. Note that you should never hold on to a BackStackEntry object; the identifier as returned by @B_android#support#v4#app#FragmentManager#BackStackEntry#getId_E@ is the only thing that will be persisted across activity instances.
